OL,7,FIt is a typically bustling afternoon in
OL,8,Fthe dusty truck yards of Karachi, the
OL,9,Fmost populous city in Pakistan and a
OL,10,Fhub of truck art ` the country's
OL,11,Fartistic identity. The air, already
OL,12,Fpolluted, is drenched with the heady
OL,13,Fscent of petrol fumes. The soundtrack
OL,14,Fis the daily cacophony ` a blare of
OL,15,Fhorns and incessant hammering, across
OL,16,Fworkshops collectively drowning out any
OL,17,Finner thoughts. But amid it all are
OL,18,Fcandy-hued trucks ` utilitarian
OL,19,Fvehicles turned into mobile oases of
OL,20,Fart and escapism, bringing colour to
OL,21,Fthe urban grind.
OL,3,CFrom planes to teapots, how kitsch
OL,4,C'truck art' took over Pakistan and
OL,5,Cbecame a global commodity
